Hearing that lately you might be getting lightheaded after walking courses and feeling cold, even in a sweater, creates concern. While it's understandable that you want to stay on track, consider your health and overall well-being. If you're consistently struggling to maintain your energy levels or feeling unwell, it might be a sign that something more serious is at play like a consistently poor diet.

It may be possible that your body is sending out warning signs that seek some attention. Instead of pushing through, it would be reasonable to try to figure out what could be the root cause behind your symptoms and if possible, if possible, reach out to a medical professional for support and guidance as they can directly assess your health. You can do a lot with diet but food can only solve so many body functions.

Additionally, it might be best to reach out to friends and family or a professional for help you work through the overwhelming urge to consistently exercise at times when you might need to be still.&#x20;
